# ╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  Alethia — environment template (community / self-host)                      ║
# ╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
#   cp .env.example .env && docker compose up -d
#
# Every value below is PRE-WIRED to the bundled docker-compose stack, so a fresh
# checkout boots unedited at http://localhost. Before exposing it to anyone, do
# two things: (1) regenerate the three [REQUIRED] secrets in §1, and (2) point
# the DB/storage at real services if you're not using the bundled ones.
#
# Legend:
#   [REQUIRED]    set this — generate a real value before any real deployment
#   [DEV-DEFAULT] works as-is for local dev; change for production
#   [OPTIONAL]    leave blank to keep the feature OFF
#
# The COMMUNITY build needs only §§1–8; it runs with the bundled stack unedited.
# The Enterprise (OpenFGA/§9) and Alethia-Labs Hosted billing (Stripe) vars below are
# OPTIONAL — leave them blank to stay on the community engine. See docs → Editions and
# docs → Self-Hosting for the full enterprise/hosted setup.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. CORE SECRETS  [REQUIRED]
# The bundled stack ships dev placeholders so it boots; generate fresh values for
# anything beyond your laptop. These three are the only secrets you MUST set.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Better Auth — signs sessions/cookies.        Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=change-me-dev-only
# [OPTIONAL] DB-backed brute-force rate limiting on /api/auth/* (sign-in / email-OTP).
# ON by default in every env; set to 0 ONLY to disable (e.g. load testing). Empty/unset
# ⇒ enabled.
# ALETHIA_AUTH_RATE_LIMIT=0
# Signs CLI device-code JWTs (shared with the runner). Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
CLI_JWT_SECRET=change-me-dev-only
# AES-256-GCM key (32-byte base64) encrypting secrets at rest: api_key connector
# secrets (Cloudflare/Vault tokens, Docker Hub PAT, …) in connector_credentials AND
# alert-channel webhook URLs. Required to connect connectors / save secret alert
# channels.                                     Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
# (dev-only sample below — replace for any real deployment.)
ALETHIA_CRED_ENCRYPTION_KEY=/MkbZwf3J4Wv++DQILEGzBChaVvow+x7U1fv5f9HZpU=
# Key id (keyring) stamped on new ciphertext — enables ONLINE key rotation. Default "1"
# if unset. Every envelope records which key sealed it, so a leaked key can be rotated
# with no downtime. Rotation flow (see lib/crypto/secrets.ts for the full runbook):
#   1. Deploy with the current key + a chosen KID, run `pnpm -F console db:reencrypt`
#      (stamps the active kid onto every existing ciphertext).
#   2. To rotate: move the old key to ALETHIA_CRED_ENCRYPTION_KEY_<oldkid> (a RETIRED key,
#      base64/32B), set a NEW ALETHIA_CRED_ENCRYPTION_KEY + a NEW KID, deploy, then run
#      `db:reencrypt` again. Keep every referenced key in the ring during the transition.
ALETHIA_CRED_ENCRYPTION_KID=1
# Retired keys (any number): ALETHIA_CRED_ENCRYPTION_KEY_<kid>=<base64/32B>. Kept so
# ciphertext sealed under a prior active key still decrypts mid-rotation. Drop a retired
# key only after `db:reencrypt` has moved every row off its kid. Example:
# ALETHIA_CRED_ENCRYPTION_KEY_1=<previous active key, base64/32B>


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. APP / WEB
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [REQUIRED] Public origin of the console. localhost for dev; your https:// URL in prod
# (used by OAuth callbacks, emails, API redirects, MCP).
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
# [OPTIONAL] Origin Better Auth runs at; falls back to NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL if unset.
BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# [OPTIONAL] Feature flag — set true to enable the design-spec canvas view.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CANVAS_ENABLED=false
# ── Self-hosted analytics (all OPTIONAL; unset = zero telemetry, OSS default) ──────────────
# PostHog — the all-in-one suite (product analytics + session replay + web-vitals + error tracking).
# One project key from posthog.com (EU cloud); host defaults to https://eu.i.posthog.com. This is what
# hosted alethialabs.io runs. The SAME key also powers server-side capture (lib/analytics/server.ts,
# used by the Stripe webhook for revenue events) — no separate server key. See deploy/analytics/posthog-runbook.md.
# HOST: set to "/ingest" in prod to use the built-in reverse-proxy (next.config.ts rewrites /ingest/* →
# eu.i.posthog.com) so ad-blockers don't drop events. Leave unset in dev → talks to EU cloud directly.
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=
# OpenReplay (session replay — watch where users get stuck). Optional OSS provider you self-host/
# bring your own Cloud project for: project key + optional ingest URL.
NEXT_PUBLIC_OPENREPLAY_PROJECT_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_OPENREPLAY_INGEST=
# OpenTelemetry traces + metrics (distributed provisioning trace enqueue→claim→…→callback, plus the
# fleet/provision metric set). UNSET = complete no-op on BOTH the console and the runner (no provider
# registered, spans/metrics cost nothing) — exactly like the analytics vars above; never a hard
# dependency, never backpressures a provision. Set to your OTLP HTTP collector to turn it on (the
# standard OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_* env is honoured — headers, per-signal endpoints, etc.). The console
# reads it in instrumentation.ts; the runner reads it in internal/obs. Must be reachable from BOTH.
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=
# service.name attribute on emitted spans/metrics (optional; defaults to "alethia-console"/"alethia-runner").
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=
# Error tracking (Sentry SDK → point it at a self-hosted GlitchTip, which speaks the Sentry protocol).
# UNSET = a complete no-op on BOTH the console (@sentry/nextjs) and the runner (sentry-go): the SDK is
# never initialized, zero overhead, never a hard dependency, and capture NEVER blocks or fails a
# request/job — exactly like the OTEL/analytics vars above. Set it to your GlitchTip/Sentry DSN to turn
# it on. Server-side only (captures uncaught server errors + the runner's job/heartbeat/claim failures);
# every event is scrubbed of secrets and tagged with trace_id/job_id so an error links to its trace.
SENTRY_DSN=
# [OPTIONAL] Deployment environment tag for Sentry events (e.g. production/staging/dev). Defaults to
# NODE_ENV on the console and "production" on the runner.
SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=
# [OPTIONAL] Sentry performance-trace sample rate [0..1] for the CONSOLE. Default 0 = error tracking
# ONLY (traces already flow through OTel above, so Sentry tracing stays off to avoid double work).
SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=
# [OPTIONAL] Structured-log verbosity for the console (pino) + runner (slog): debug|info|warn|error
# (default info). Purely operational logs — independent of the OTEL export above.
ALETHIA_LOG_LEVEL=
# [OPTIONAL] Operator org that receives PLATFORM-health alerts (system.platform.*): a background loop
# (job recovery / fleet scaler / alerts / connection sweep / reconcile) going DEGRADED — i.e. not
# succeeding within N× its interval — raises a throttled `system.platform.loop_degraded` alert to this
# org's configured channels (and `loop_recovered` when it comes back). UNSET = the degradation is still
# logged + surfaced in /api/health, we just don't fan out to a channel. Set to the operator/ops org id.
ALETHIA_PLATFORM_ALERT_ORG_ID=
# [OPTIONAL] Target for in-app "Docs" links (defaults to the bundled docs site).
DOCS_URL=
# [DEV-DEFAULT] Host port for the optional bundled DB UI:
#   docker compose --profile tools up -d pgweb  → http://localhost:8081
ALETHIA_PGWEB_PORT=8081
# [DEV-DEFAULT] Self-managed is the community default; the app runs the community
# build. (`hosted` enables Stripe billing — an Alethia-Labs SaaS concern; see docs.)
ALETHIA_DEPLOYMENT_MODE=self-managed


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. DATABASE (Postgres)  [DEV-DEFAULT]
# Defaults target the bundled `postgres` service. Two roles: the migration/service
# URL (bypasses RLS — runner/CLI/RPC paths) and the app URL (least-privilege,
# RLS-enforced — user-facing queries). The app role is created by the first
# migration. Point these at a managed Postgres for a hosted deploy.
# Host port 5433 avoids colliding with a host-native Postgres on 5432.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ALETHIA_DATABASE_URL=postgres://alethia:alethia-dev-secret@localhost:5433/alethia
ALETHIA_APP_DATABASE_URL=postgres://alethia_app:alethia-app-dev-secret@localhost:5433/alethia
# Bundled-Postgres knobs (compose only).
ALETHIA_DB_USER=alethia
ALETHIA_DB_PASSWORD=alethia-dev-secret
ALETHIA_DB_NAME=alethia
ALETHIA_DB_PORT=5433
# Password for the least-privilege app role created by the first migration.
ALETHIA_APP_DB_PASSWORD=alethia-app-dev-secret
# [OPTIONAL] Connection-pool tuning (postgres-js). Defaults: max 10, idle 20s.
# ALETHIA_DB_POOL_MAX=10
# ALETHIA_DB_IDLE_TIMEOUT=20


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. OBJECT STORAGE (S3-compatible)  [DEV-DEFAULT]
# Terraform/OpenTofu state + plan artifacts. Defaults target the bundled SeaweedFS.
# For a hosted deploy, point at AWS S3 / R2 / Garage and set
# ALETHIA_STORAGE_AUTO_CREATE_BUCKETS=false (pre-provision the buckets out of band).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ALETHIA_STORAGE_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:8333
ALETHIA_STORAGE_REGION=us-east-1
ALETHIA_STORAGE_ACCESS_KEY_ID=alethia
ALETHIA_STORAGE_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=alethia-dev-secret
# App creates the buckets it needs on first use (self-host default). false for managed S3.
ALETHIA_STORAGE_AUTO_CREATE_BUCKETS=true
# Host port the bundled SeaweedFS S3 API is published on (compose only).
ALETHIA_STORAGE_PORT=8333


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. OAUTH PROVIDERS  [OPTIONAL]
# Only the providers you configure appear on the sign-in screen. (GitHub & Google
# are native; GitLab & Bitbucket via the generic OAuth plugin.) With none set,
# sign-in falls back to email OTP.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# GitLab instance for OAuth + API (default https://gitlab.com; set for self-hosted GitLab).
GITLAB_BASE_URL=
GITLAB_APPLICATION_ID=
GITLAB_SECRET=
BITBUCKET_KEY=
BITBUCKET_SECRET=


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. TRANSACTIONAL EMAIL (AWS SES)  [OPTIONAL]
# Unset → sign-in codes / emails are logged to the server console (fine for dev).
# Set ALETHIA_SES_REGION to enable; from-addresses must be verified SES identities
# (account out of the SES sandbox to mail arbitrary recipients). Credentials use
# ALETHIA_SES_* when set, else the AWS default chain (IAM role / AWS_* env;
# AWS_REGION is the region fallback). Quote the from-addresses — the angle brackets
# otherwise trip `source .env`. Full runbook: docs → Self-Hosting → Email.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ALETHIA_SES_REGION=
ALETHIA_SES_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
ALETHIA_SES_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AUTH_EMAIL_FROM="Alethia <no-reply@auth.alethialabs.io>"
EMAIL_FROM="Alethia <hello@mail.alethialabs.io>"
# Per-stream SES configuration sets (optional). Tag sends so bounce/complaint
# events route to SNS → /api/webhooks/ses → the suppression list. Created by the
# infra/email-ses OpenTofu stack (`tofu output configuration_set_names`).
ALETHIA_SES_AUTH_CONFIG_SET=
ALETHIA_SES_GENERAL_CONFIG_SET=
# Inbox the hosted in-app feedback widget emails to (hosted-only; defaults to
# feedback@alethialabs.io). Self-managed builds link to GitHub issues instead.
FEEDBACK_EMAIL=


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. AI ASSISTANT & COST  [OPTIONAL]
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The AI assistant (Ask AI / agent) now talks DIRECTLY to the model providers via the
# AI SDK provider packages — no Vercel AI Gateway. Set the provider key(s) your model
# config needs; without them the routes return 503 and the UI shows a "not configured"
# state. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is required for the default (all-Anthropic) config.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Only needed if you point a role/override at an openai/* model (see AI_EXECUTOR_MODEL).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Curated client-picker override (allowlisted: anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5,
# anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6). Defaults to Haiku 4.5 (cheapest tool-capable model).
# AI_MODEL=anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5
# Per-role model overrides in `provider/native-id` form — swap a role with no rebuild.
# Executor = the cheap tool-loop model (default anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5). Point it at
# OpenAI with e.g. AI_EXECUTOR_MODEL=openai/gpt-5-mini (also set OPENAI_API_KEY).
# AI_EXECUTOR_MODEL=anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5
# Advisor = the planning/review model on step 0 (by AI tier).
# AI_ADVISOR_MODEL_PLUS=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6
# AI_ADVISOR_MODEL_MAX=anthropic/claude-opus-4-8
# DEPRECATED: the Vercel AI Gateway was removed — AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY is no longer read.
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=
# Infracost API key enables cost estimation in the runner.
INFRACOST_API_KEY=
#
# Remote MCP server: exposes the agent's read + scan tools to Claude / claude.ai
# at <BETTER_AUTH_URL>/api/mcp over OAuth 2.1 (Better Auth's mcp() plugin — no
# extra config; reuses BETTER_AUTH_SECRET/URL). Self-host = always enabled. Add
# the connector in claude.ai with the /api/mcp URL.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. SELF-HOSTED RUNNER  [OPTIONAL]
# Only needed if you run provisioning jobs. The runner talks to the console over
# HTTP + S3 only. Skip this whole section to just use the web UI.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Console URL the runner calls back to (must be reachable from where the runner runs).
ALETHIA_WEB_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
# Operator: `self` (runs in your cloud with native perms) — the self-host default.
# (Legacy ALETHIA_RUNNER_MODE=self-hosted still works as a back-compat fallback.)
ALETHIA_RUNNER_OPERATOR=self
# Credentials from registering the runner in the console (Settings → Runners).
ALETHIA_RUNNER_ID=
ALETHIA_RUNNER_TOKEN=
# Concurrent jobs per runner (N worker subprocesses). Default 1.
# ALETHIA_RUNNER_SLOTS=1
# Restrict this runner to specific clouds (comma-separated, e.g. "aws,gcp").
# Empty = any provider (the full multi-cloud image).
# ALETHIA_RUNNER_PROVIDERS=
# Override the bootstrap dedup id (default: Hetzner metadata, then hostname). Set a
# unique value per process to run several runners on one host (e.g. `pnpm dev:runner`
# sets dev-runner-1 / dev-runner-2 so each self-registers as a distinct runner).
# ALETHIA_RUNNER_INSTANCE_ID=
#
# Managed runner-fleet autoscaling (FLEET_*): the in-app scaler can provision warm
# runner VMs on Hetzner. See docs → Self-Hosting → Configuration.
# Shared bearer the fleet's cloud-init runners present to self-register (no per-runner
# creds): the console's /api/runners/bootstrap accepts it and mints real credentials.
# Needed for the managed/Hetzner fleet, and for local runners via `pnpm dev:runner`
# (which generates one into .env on first run). Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# ALETHIA_RUNNER_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN=
#
# Fleet scaler knobs (only when FLEET_PROVIDER=hcloud). Pools themselves live in the
# DB (fleet_pools — seed via Settings → Runners or SQL); these are process-wide.
# FLEET_PROVIDER=hcloud            # unset/`manual` = scaler is a no-op
# HCLOUD_SSH_KEYS=                 # comma-separated Hetzner SSH key IDs for fleet VMs
# HCLOUD_SERVER_TYPE=cax21         # Arm shared vCPU — cheapest fleet tier
# HCLOUD_IMAGE=ubuntu-24.04
# FLEET_RUNNER_IMAGE_TAG=latest    # per-cloud runner image tag (or pin a version)
# FLEET_RUNNER_SLOTS=1             # concurrent jobs per fleet VM
# FLEET_BOOT_GRACE_SECONDS=180     # reap window for VMs that never self-register
#
# Carry-your-own cloud tokens for "token clouds" (only when this runner provisions
# them). AWS / GCP / Azure use per-job role assumption instead — no static keys here.
# HCLOUD_TOKEN=
# DIGITALOCEAN_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# CIVO_TOKEN=
# Alibaba needs NO platform credentials: the console assumes the customer RAM role via
# AssumeRoleWithOIDC with an assertion minted by the OIDC issuer (ALETHIA_OIDC_SIGNING_KEY) —
# no Alibaba account, no AccessKey.
#
# Platform-internal secret — Bearer token used for runner registration / release
# APIs. Needed only if you wire up runner self-registration. openssl rand -hex 32
RELEASE_API_SECRET=
# [OPTIONAL] Bearer secret enabling the manual maintenance endpoints (alert-delivery
# sweep, fleet scaler, cloud-connection reconciliation sweep). Unset = those endpoints
# fail closed; the in-process alert scheduler and job-recovery loops run regardless.
# Cloud connections: the reconciliation sweep now runs IN-PROCESS by default (keeps health + the asset
# inventory fresh + backfills). This secret only gates the OPTIONAL external cron route
# POST /api/internal/connections/sweep (hosted) — not required for the in-app sweep.
# ALSO gates the DEEP-DETAIL of GET /api/health: a caller sending `Authorization: Bearer <this>` gets
# the full readiness document (DB latency, per-loop counters, OTel endpoint); anonymous callers get only
# the sanitized aggregate {status} (+ the same HTTP code, so LB readiness probes still work). Unset =
# the detail is never exposed (fail-closed) but the aggregate + liveness (?probe=live) stay public.
# openssl rand -hex 32
ALETHIA_CRON_SECRET=

# [OPTIONAL] Days a soft-removed inventory row (a resource deleted in-cloud) is kept before the sweep
# garbage-collects it. Disconnecting a connection purges its inventory immediately regardless. Default 7.
ALETHIA_INVENTORY_RETENTION_DAYS=7

# [INFO] AWS/GCP/Alibaba need NO platform config — they're KEYLESS and issuer-direct: the customer's IAM
# role / WIF pool / RAM OIDC provider trusts the Alethia OIDC issuer (${APP_URL}/api/oidc) directly, so the
# console + runner federate with a minted assertion. Availability tracks the issuer key (below); nothing to
# set here. (Only Azure needs an app id — next.)
# Azure is KEYLESS: register ONE multi-tenant Entra app with a federated-identity credential
# trusting the Alethia OIDC issuer (${APP_URL}/api/oidc, subject alethia-connector, audience
# api://AzureADTokenExchange) — NO client secret and NO platform Entra app. The customer's setup
# script creates a user-assigned managed identity in their own subscription (its client id stored
# per connection); the console + runner authenticate AS it. Nothing to set here — availability tracks
# the OIDC issuer key, parity with AWS/GCP/Alibaba.
# GCP: the WIF subject-token source is supplied by the deployment's identity (the stored
# per-connection WIF config references it); no static GCP secret is stored here.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 9. OPENFGA — fine-grained authorization (ENTERPRISE)  [OPTIONAL]
# Off by default: with both URL+store unset the community PostgresRbacPDP is the
# engine. Set BOTH OPENFGA_API_URL and OPENFGA_STORE_ID to switch to OpenFGA.
# Two paths to run it locally:
#   • `pnpm dev:up` (native console) AUTO-provisions a store, writes API_URL/STORE_ID
#     to the gitignored apps/console/.env.local, and overrides them at localhost:8082
#     — so leave the two vars below BLANK for dev:up.
#   • Full docker:  docker compose --profile enterprise up -d openfga
#     then create a store and paste its id into OPENFGA_STORE_ID (no compose helper):
#       curl -X POST http://localhost:8082/stores -H 'content-type: application/json' \
#            -d '{"name":"alethia"}'
#     In-cluster the console reaches it at OPENFGA_API_URL=http://openfga:8080.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPENFGA_API_URL=
OPENFGA_STORE_ID=
# [OPTIONAL] Pin a specific authorization model; the latest is used when unset.
OPENFGA_MODEL_ID=
# Password for the bundled OpenFGA Postgres (enterprise compose profile).
OPENFGA_DB_PASSWORD=openfga-dev-secret
# Host port the bundled OpenFGA HTTP API is published on (8082 avoids pgweb's 8081).
OPENFGA_HTTP_PORT=8082


# ─── Billing (Stripe) — Alethia-Labs Hosted ──────────────────────────────────────
# Console checkout/billing and the marketing /pricing page read live prices from
# Stripe. Unset (STRIPE_SECRET_KEY) = no paid plans (community build); the public
# pricing page falls back to the static catalog label. Keys at https://dashboard.stripe.com.
# Run `pnpm -F console stripe:setup` to create the products/prices/meter and fill the
# STRIPE_PRICE_* below (idempotent; works for test + live — see the script header).
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# Verifies inbound Stripe webhook signatures (whsec_…). Required with STRIPE_SECRET_KEY.
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Client-side publishable key (pk_…) for the embedded Payment Element. Safe to expose.
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# Pro plan's per-seat Stripe Price (price_…). The only self-serve paid price.
STRIPE_PRICE_TEAM=
# [OPTIONAL] Enterprise is invoiced off-Stripe (granted via scripts/set-org-plan.mjs),
# so this is normally unset. Set it only if you sell Enterprise as a Stripe subscription.
STRIPE_PRICE_ENTERPRISE=
# [OPTIONAL] Graduated metered Price IDs for managed-runner job-minutes per plan.
# Unset → usage is surfaced but not billed through Stripe (metering opt-in).
STRIPE_PRICE_METER_TEAM=
STRIPE_PRICE_METER_ENTERPRISE=
# [OPTIONAL] Standalone AI product subscription Price IDs (separate from the org plan —
# lib/billing/ai-plan.ts). AI Free needs no price (everyone's free allowance); set these to
# sell AI Plus / AI Max as their own Stripe subscription that raises the AI credit caps.
STRIPE_PRICE_AI_PLUS=
STRIPE_PRICE_AI_MAX=
# [OPTIONAL] Set true to compute tax + collect VAT/Tax IDs at checkout (Stripe Tax).
# Requires Stripe Tax origin + registrations configured first, or Checkout errors.
STRIPE_TAX_ENABLED=false

# [OPTIONAL] Odoo фактура API (management/infra/odoo — books.alethialabs.io). When both are
# set (hosted), a paid Stripe invoice is issued as a branded Bulgarian фактура in Odoo, whose
# PDF + legal number become the customer's invoice of record (attached to the receipt +
# mirrored). Unset → the app falls back to Stripe's own PDF. Token = alethia_stripe.api_token.
ODOO_INVOICE_URL=
ODOO_INVOICE_TOKEN=

# ─── Hosted marketing site (apps/marketing) ──────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Canonical origin for the marketing site's robots.txt / sitemap.xml
# absolute URLs. Defaults to https://alethialabs.io.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=
# [OPTIONAL] Base URL the console's legal links (Terms / Privacy in the auth footer)
# point at — the legal pages live in the marketing app, not the console, so a
# self-hosted console links out to the hosted legal pages. Defaults to
# https://alethialabs.io. Set "" for same-origin /terms when you also run marketing
# behind your console domain.
NEXT_PUBLIC_LEGAL_URL=
# [OPTIONAL] Issue tracker the self-managed account menu's "Report an issue" links to
# (the hosted build shows an in-app feedback dialog instead). Defaults to the public
# Alethia repo's new-issue page.
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEEDBACK_REPO_URL=

# ─── Cloud connectors (apps/console) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Origin that serves the connector setup artifacts the connect flows hand
# out: the AWS CloudFormation template (alethia-bootstrap.yaml) and the GCP/Azure
# Cloud Shell scripts (alethia-{gcp,azure}-setup.sh). Defaults to the hosted
# public-read bucket (provisioned by infra/connector-assets):
# https://alethia-connector-assets.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com — a self-host can point
# this at its own console origin instead (the same files ship in apps/console/public/),
# e.g. NEXT_PUBLIC_CONNECTOR_ASSETS_ORIGIN=https://alethia.example.com. Note: the AWS
# CloudFormation quick-create flow requires an S3-hosted template URL, so AWS self-host
# either keeps the bucket default or uses the Terraform method.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONNECTOR_ASSETS_ORIGIN=

# ─── Support (apps/console) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Where new-case notifications and customer replies are mirrored for the
# Alethia help-desk. SUPPORT_EMAIL defaults to support@alethialabs.io; the Slack
# webhook is a no-op when unset (OSS self-host sends nothing).
SUPPORT_EMAIL=
SUPPORT_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=

# ─── Admin (internal staff dashboard, apps/admin) ────────────────────────────────
# The internal STAFF support dashboard is a separate app on its own subdomain, gated by
# Cloudflare Access (like the Umami dashboard) — NOT Better Auth. Access forwards the
# verified caller in Cf-Access-Authenticated-User-Email; the allowlist below AUTHORIZES it.
# [REQUIRED for admin] Comma-separated staff emails allowed into the dashboard.
SUPPORT_STAFF_EMAILS=
# [OPTIONAL] Local-dev fallback identity used when the Cloudflare Access header is absent
# (no tunnel in front). Ignored in production. Must also be listed in SUPPORT_STAFF_EMAILS.
SUPPORT_ADMIN_DEV_EMAIL=
# [OPTIONAL] Customer-facing console origin — the base for the deep links in staff
# notification emails (they point at the CONSOLE case page the customer reads),
# e.g. https://alethialabs.io.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONSOLE_URL=

# ─── Platform-operator plane (Enterprise onboarding) ────────────────────────────────────────
# The staff app (apps/admin /orgs) onboards Enterprise customers by calling console-owned
# provisioning routes (/api/internal/platform/{provision-org,set-plan}). These mint orgs + invite
# owners + activate plans, so they use a DEDICATED bearer secret — NOT the broadly-shared
# ALETHIA_CRON_SECRET — and are inert (503) when it's unset.
# [REQUIRED for the operator plane] Shared bearer between apps/admin and the console.
PLATFORM_PROVISION_SECRET=
# [REQUIRED for the operator plane] Permanent system user = the `inviterId` on operator-issued owner
# invitations. Seeded on first use; deleting it cascades pending invites.
PLATFORM_SYSTEM_USER_EMAIL=
# [REQUIRED to ACT] Operator allowlist — DISTINCT from the read-only SUPPORT_STAFF_EMAILS (being able
# to READ cross-tenant is not being able to ACT). Only these emails can flip/create Enterprise orgs.
PLATFORM_ADMIN_EMAILS=
# [REQUIRED for the Stripe onboarding path] Stripe Product id enterprise line items reference
# (subscription price_data needs a product; Enterprise has no catalog price).
STRIPE_ENTERPRISE_PRODUCT_ID=

# ─── Break-glass (privileged incident recovery, /api/breakglass/* + `alethia ops`) ──────────
# The most security-sensitive surface: audited, gated, blast-radius-bounded RLS-bypassing recovery
# actions for on-call operators. Its own auth boundary — SEPARATE from the read-only support-staff
# gate above (being able to READ cross-tenant is not being able to ACT).
# [MASTER SWITCH] Default-OFF: unset (or anything but "true") ⇒ the whole surface 404s / refuses.
ALETHIA_BREAKGLASS_ENABLED=
# [REQUIRED to act] Comma-separated operator emails allowed to perform break-glass actions. This is
# a DISTINCT allowlist from SUPPORT_STAFF_EMAILS — keep it tiny. In production the operator UI should
# additionally sit behind its OWN dedicated Cloudflare Access application (not the support-admin one).
BREAKGLASS_OPERATORS=
# [OPTIONAL] Local-dev fallback identity when neither a CF-Access header nor a CLI bearer is present.
# Ignored unless also listed in BREAKGLASS_OPERATORS. Never set in production.
BREAKGLASS_DEV_EMAIL=
# [OPTIONAL, spoofing defense] Shared secret the dedicated break-glass Cloudflare-Access proxy injects
# as X-Breakglass-Proxy-Secret. The CF-Access email header is trusted ONLY when this matches — so a
# spoofed header sent straight to the console origin (which is NOT behind CF Access) is rejected. When
# unset, the CF-Access path is DISABLED and only the cryptographic CLI bearer path works (fail-closed).
BREAKGLASS_ACCESS_PROXY_SECRET=
# [OPTIONAL, default-off, INDEPENDENT arming] The cross-cloud orphan force-destroy (orphan_clean)
# ships INERT/fail-closed and refuses even with a valid two-person approval unless this is "true".
# (Even armed it currently returns "not implemented" rather than an unscoped delete — see actions.ts.)
ALETHIA_BREAKGLASS_ORPHAN_CLEAN_ENABLED=
# [OPTIONAL, RUNNER-side, default-off] The STATE_SURGERY job's runner executor is INERT: unless a
# runner sets this to "true" it refuses (no state touched). Even armed it is unimplemented (fail-closed).
ALETHIA_BREAKGLASS_STATE_SURGERY_ENABLED=
